Polaris MF to Acquire Yuanta Futures in NT$3.8 Billion Swap

-- B y   A d e l a   L i n
-- 
2011-08-16T11:05:16Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-16/polaris-mf-to-acquire-yuanta-futures-in-nt-3-8-billion-swap.html
Polaris MF Global Futures Co. plans
to acquire  Yuanta Futures Co.  in a share swap worth almost
NT$3.8 billion ($131 million) to create  Taiwan ’s largest futures
company.  Each share of Yuanta, a wholly owned unit of Yuanta
Financial Holding Co., will be exchanged for 1.01 Polaris MF
shares, the companies said in a joint statement today. The
acquisition is expected to be completed by April 1, 2012, and
the new entity will have combined assets of NT$41.3 billion
according to the statement.  “Polaris will issue new shares for the swap and Yuanta
Financial Holding will hold about 68 percent of the merged
entity,” YD Chuang, executive vice president of Yuanta
Financial, said by telephone today.  Polaris MF plans to issue 101 million new shares as part of
the transaction, it said in a separate statement to the local
stock exchange. At Polaris MF closing price today the new shares
are worth NT$3.8 billion.  Yuanta Financial in April agreed to buy Polaris Securities
Co. for $1.7 billion in cash and shares to expand its brokerage
business. Polaris Securities owns 44.5 percent of Polaris MF,
Kuo Yu-hong, executive vice president of Polaris MF said by
telephone today.  Before the announcement, Polaris MF Global shares rose 1
percent to NT$37.30 at the close in Taipei trading and Yuanta
Financial advanced 0.6 percent to NT$18.40. Polaris Securities
fell 0.5 percent to NT$20.15.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Adela Lin in Taipei at 
